 select category how to learn singing   mix singing   professional singing   reviews   singing myths   singing technique   uncategorized   recent posts what is talent in singing how do i sing better should i give up singing yes… how to belt properly why does the voice crack how to prevent it robert lunte review the four pillars of singing rex february   how to learn singing  reviews tweet program the four pillars of singing product type singing program company the vocalist studio founder robert lunte price from  my rating  out of      the four pillars of singing – product overview there are many singing programs on the internet and one of my favoritewhich is very few is robert lunte’s the four pillars of singing you have to understand that i come from the mix school of singing something that is very different from or even opposite of  robert lunte’s method more than a year ago i decided to try something different to see what coaches from other singing schools have to say about singing so i decided to join robert’s program for one year boy was i impressed  one of the most complete singing program online if you simply visit robert lunte’s website of the vocalist studio you’d be impressed with what you see there you will see different packages of singing training with combinations of the online training program the four pillars of singing the hard copy and ebook of the program and private singing lessons with robert himself in order not to get overwhelmed by everything that’s offered on the website let’s just focus on the entry package of the online course and system the four pillars of singing   highdef training videos – lectures  training routines since i had joined this singing program for a year i can give you an inside look and my user experience with the four pillars of singing basically it’s a website with more than  highquality training videos that you can watch and practice singing with robert is very professional with his video production and since he’s always demonstrating when he’s teaching in the videos the sound quality is superb i’m involved in music production at work so i can assure you it’s very comfortable watching those videos with robert explaining his singing method since we’re not interested with just watching videos i can tell you that the most important thing which is the content is very comprehensive and easytofollow without losing depth and sophisticated details when you train with the videos the videos are catergorized into several sections starting with lectures on singing myths and the tvs methodology explaining each onset trainings that help to build vocal coordination and muscular strengths then it has an extensive video section on training routinesa lot of them in which robert walks you through all the exercises he sings them with you and that’s where you’ll hear and see him hitting high cs and above in full voice basically the coordination training gets you to balance out the registers and get good tone quality in your voice and the strengthbuilding training works out your vocal muscle to get your voice stronger and higher  the four pillars of singing – the book and ebook the program also comes with a book also called the four pillars of singing which is a page book that fully explains his method and training routines but if you want to get the book it cost a lot more than just joining the website for me the training website is already good enough for me which only cost  for one year of access i paid  for the ebook and the website because that was the entry package offer back then   robert lunte – the vocal coach and the method while i don’t  agree or follow his method i have to say that robert is a master of vocal pedagogy his knowledge of singing technique is not only vast and complete he also has a gift of breaking down very complicated concepts of singing pedagogy into simple terms that anyone can understand i was introduced by robert the concept of onsetshow you start a sound and its importance in vocal training through his videos he uses  different onsets to train singers for vocal coordination and strength building each serves a different purpose he is one of the few vocal coachesif not the only from the belt school that trains bridging and connecting because usually the teacher is either one or the other – beltbottomup or bridge and connecttopdown he does a superb job in combining these two most important aspect of singing in his methodology which is very rare because teachers from both schools don’t like or agree with each other in the end the students get all the benefits   live chat with robert himself when you visit his website there is a little window on the bottom right that says “live chat” which means robert is around to talk with you or “leave a question” when he’s not around that little window was where i got acquainted with robert personally he is very responsive with chats and questions – he answered almost everytime i asked a question although i discontinued my membership due to busy personal schedulei started grad school and work fulltime at the same time he still answers my emails whenever i write to him conclusion if my personal singing technique was not so deeply rooted in mix i would choose robert’s singing system the four pillars of singing to train myself because it’s just so complete and deals with almost every aspect of singing i’m just very impressed with the system he has built it’s not easy to come up with your own system and robert did it i was very skeptical before joining since i don’t like it when a teacher is trying to be original with an ancient art but i must say as an experienced and advanced singer i was very impresseddid i say that already with his system after joining – robert is not inventing something new he’s systemizing it in a new and innovative way that anyone in the modern world could learn and benefit from his singing system if you have any questions or comments please leave a message and i’ll be happy to discuss with you   leave a reply cancel reply your email address will not be published required fields are marked commentname email website     singer corporation  wikipedia singer corporation from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search singer corporation founded  as i m singer company new york new york united states headquarters la vergne tennessee usa parent svp worldwide international semi tech microsystems  website singercom a singer treadle sewing machine singer corporation is an american manufacturer of sewing machines first established as i m singer  co in  by isaac merritt singer with new york lawyer edward clark best known for its sewing machines it was renamed singer manufacturing company in  then the singer company in  it is based in la vergne tennessee near nashville its first large factory for mass production was built in elizabeth new jersey in  contents  the company  early sales figures  singer in scotland  world war ii  marketing  diversification  st century  singer buildings  list of company presidents  four best selling domestic singer sewing machines  see also  references  further reading  external links the companyedit old singer logo a singer  sewing machine singer’s original design which was the first practical sewing machine for general domestic use incorporated the basic eyepointed needle and lock stitch developed by elias howe who won a patentinfringement suit against singer in  patent no  of august   introduced one of the most useful machines and one of the most remarkable men that have figured in the development of the sewing machine isaac merritt singer strolling player theater manager inventor and millionaire brought into the business a new machine and novel methods of exploitation which gave a powerful impulse to the youthful industry the singer improvements met the demand of the tailoring and leather industries for a heavier and more powerful machine singer consolidated enough patents in the field to enable him to engage in mass production and by  his company was the largest manufacturer of sewing machines in the world in  singer produced its first vibrating shuttle sewing machine an improvement over contemporary transverse shuttle designs see bobbin drivers singer began to market its machines internationally in  and won first prize at the paris world’s fair the company demonstrated the first workable electric sewing machine at the philadelphia electric exhibition in  and began massproducing domestic electric machines in  singer was also a marketing innovator and was a pioneer in promoting the use of installment payment plans early sales figuresedit source year       units       by  singer was claiming cumulative sales of  million machines and displaying the  millionth in philadelphia singer in scotlandedit workers leaving singer sewing machine factory on clydebank in  the singer company decided that the demand for their sewing machines in the uk was sufficiently high to open a local factory in john street glasgow was selected for its iron making industries cheap labor and possibly because at the time the general manager of the us singer sewing machine company was george mckenzie who was of scottish descent demand for sewing machines outstripped production at the new plant and by  a new larger factory was completed in james street bridgeton by now singer employed over  people in scotland but still they could not produce enough machines in  george mckenzie presidentelect of the singer sewing machine company undertook the ground breaking ceremony on  acres of farmland at kilbowie clydebank originally two main buildings were constructed each foot  m long foot  m wide and  storeys high these were connected by three wings built above the middle wing was a huge foot  m tall clock tower with the ‘singer’ name clearly displayed for all to see for miles around  miles  km of railway lines were laid through the factory to connect the different departments such as the boiler room foundry and shipping and to lines to main railway stations sir robert mcalpine was the building contractor and the factory was designed to be fire proof with water sprinklers making it the most modern factory in europe at that time with nearly a million square feet of space and almost  employees it was possible to produce on average  machines a week making it the largest sewing machine factory in the world the clydebank factory was so productive that in  the us singer company set up the singer manufacturing company ltd as a uk registered company demand continued to exceed production so each building was extended upwards to  stories high in the first world war sewing machine production gave way to munitions the singer clydebank factory received over  government contracts and made  million artillery shells shell components fuses and aeroplane parts as well as grenades rifle parts and  horseshoes its labor force of  was about  female at wars end from its opening in  until  the kilbowie factory produced approximately  sewing machines singer was the world leader and sold more machines than all the other makers added together in  the factory shipped  million machines the late s and s saw a period of significant change at the clydebank factory in  singer reduced production at their main american plant and transferred  of this production to the clydebank factory in a bid to reduce costs between  and  the clydebank factory underwent a £ million modernization program which saw the clydebank factory cease the production of cast iron machines and focus on the production of aluminium machines for western markets as part of this modernisation programme the famous singer clock was demolished in  at the height of its productiveness in the mid s singer employed over  workers but by the end of that decade compulsory redundancies were taking place and  years later the workforce was down to  financial problems and lack of orders forced the world’s largest sewing machine factory to close in june  bringing to an end over  years of sewing machine production in scotland the complex of buildings was demolished in  world war iiedit painted singer sewing sign in kingston ny a singer sewing machine with electric retrofit during world war ii the company suspended sewing machine production to take on government contracts for weapons manufacturing factories in the us supplied the american forces with norden bomb sights and m carbine rifle receivers while factories in germany provided their armed forces with weapons in  the company was given a production study by the government to draw plans and develop standard raw material sizes for building ma pistols the following april  singer was given an educational order of  units with serial numbers s – s the educational order was a program set up by the us ordnance board to teach companies without gunmaking experience to manufacture weapons after the  units were delivered to the government the management decided to produce artillery and bomb sights the pistol tooling and manufacturing machines were transferred to remington rand whilst some went to the ithaca gun company original singer pistols are collectable and in excellent condition sell for  to  with the highest paid  at auction in  marketingedit the singer sewing machine was the first complex standardized technology to be mass marketed it was not the first sewing machine and its patent in  led to a patent battle with elias howe inventor of the lockstitch machine this eventually resulted in a patent sharing accord among the major firms marketing strategies included focusing on the manufacturing industry gender identity credit plans and “hire purchases” singers marketing emphasized the role of women and their relationship to the home evoking ideals of virtue modesty and diligence though the sewing machine represented liberation from arduous hand sewing it chiefly benefited those sewing for their families and themselves tradespeople relying on sewing as a livelihood still suffered from poor wages which dropped further in response to the time savings gained by machine sewing singer offered credit purchases and renttoown arrangements allowing people to rent a machine with the rental payments applied to the eventual purchase of the machine and sold globally through the use of directsales doortodoor canvassers to demonstrate and sell the machines diversificationedit singer in malta in the s the company diversified acquiring the friden calculator company in  packard bell electronics in  and general precision equipment corporation in  gpe included librascope the kearfott company inc and link flight simulation in the  also singer bought out gps systems and added it to the link simulations systems division lssd this unit produced nuclear power plant control center simulators in silver spring md while flight simulators were produced in binghamton new york in  corporate raider paul bilzerian made a greenmail run at singer and ended up owning the company when no white knight rescuer appeared to recover his money bilzerian sold off parts of the company kearfott was split the kearfott guidance  navigation corporation was sold to the astronautics corporation of america in  and the electronic systems division was purchased by gecmarconi in  renamed gecmarconi electronic systems and later incorporated into bae systems the four link divisions developing and supporting industrial and flight simulation were sold to canadian avionics engineering cae and became caelink the sewing machine division was sold in  to semitech microelectronics a publicly traded torontobased company for several years in the s singer set up a national sales force for cat phototypesetting machines of unix troff fame made by another massachusetts company graphic systems inc this division was purchased by wang laboratories in  st centuryedit woman with singer sewing machine in east timor  the singer corporation produces a range of consumer products including electronic sewing machines it is now part of svp worldwide which also owns the pfaff and husqvarna viking brands which is in turn owned by kohlberg  company which bought singer in  its main competitors are brother industries janome aisin seiki—a toyota group company that manufactures toyota necchi and er classic sewing machines and juki singer buildingsedit singer was heavily involved in manhattan real estate in the s through edward clark a founder of the company clark had built the dakota apartments and other manhattan buildings in the s in  the singer company retained ernest flagg to build a story loft building at broadway and prince street in lower manhattan the building is now considered architecturally notable and has been restored the story singer building completed in  was also designed by flagg who designed two landmark residences for bourne constructed during bournes tenure the singer building demolished in  was then the tallest building in the world and was the tallest building to be intentionally demolished until the twin towers of the world trade center were destroyed in the september  attacks at their clydebank scotland factory singer built a  ft clock tower which stood over the central wing and had the reputation of being the largest fourfaced clock in the world each face weighed five tons and it took four men fifteen minutes twice a week to keep it wound singer railway station built to serve the factory is still in existence to this day the famous singer house designed by architect pavel suzor was built in – at nevsky prospekt in saint petersburg for headquarters of the russian branch of the company this modern style building situated just opposite to the kazan cathedral is officially recognized as an object of russian historicalcultural heritage list of company presidentsedit isaac singer – inslee hopper – edward c clark – george ross mckenzie – frederick gilbert bourne – sir douglas alexander – milton c lightner – donald p kircher – joseph bernard flavin – paul bilzerian